## Rules

- Use dateUtils.js functions for all date formatting and manipulation; always use formatDate for database operations, formatDateTimeForDisplay for user-facing timestamps, and getMonthDateRange for month date range calculations.

## Technologies

- HTML/CSS/JS
- EJS
- Express
- PostgreSQL
- Tailwind CSS

## APP look

- App should be focused on User experience
- Clean and simple look
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling

## Linting

- ESLint is configured for `.js` files and `<script>` tags in `.ejs` files
- Run `npm run lint` to check all files, `npm run lint:fix` to auto-fix issues
- Files with EJS template syntax inside JavaScript code (like `<% users.forEach %>` in arrays) cannot be parsed by ESLint and must be added to the `ignores` array in `eslint.config.js`
- Currently ignored EJS files: `views/admin/groups.ejs`, `views/admin/statistics.ejs`, `views/work-hours/index.ejs`
- If you get "Parsing error: Unexpected token <" in an EJS file, add it to the ignores list
